You are about to install PortaBrowseInstall32

It gives you the choice of installing Firefox, Palemoon and/or Seamonkey
to any harddrive or flashdrive and running from there, saving ram.
It will remember this drive even if the drive name changes.

Click "Portable Browser Installer" on the Internet menu.

In older Puppy's you may need to install a newer Yad:

http://distro.ibiblio.org/puppylinux/pet_packages-common32/yad-0.40.3-i686_common32.pet

close this message and you will be given the choice to install this yad if needed.